caption: Service was amazing. Food was great for the price. Very satisfied.
The wait was long and the food was terrible. Burnt everything. Who makes lo mein with angel hair pasta?
Terrific prices and great delivery service.  Strongly recommend eating there
Good food,reasonably priced, very friendly staff. They remember your order after first visit!!!
This is my favorite spot to get Bahn Mi's
Chinese food and the feeling at this place is great. The staff was very sociable and kind.
chinese food and the setting here is super good. Service is always awesome even when they have a full house. The service was very friendly and attentive. This place has an awesome feel to it.

Everytime I make roadtrip into nola, this place is a pitstop. A hole in the wall, but every bit as good as similar family-run places in New York, and frankly better than any I had 12 years living in San Francisco.

This is a great family owned business with authentic food.  K.T., Hang and their brother run this business and learned from their mother who recently passed.  They have spruced up and painted their 200 to 300 yr old building which exudes the character of the french quarter.  The food is excellent, i said excellent and it comes with a smile.  I have been traveling here and eating at moon wok  for years.  My daughter who lives in NOLA now is a frequent flyer at moon wok.  The charcoal pork chop dinner is excellent and very reasonable.  Actually you cant go wrong eating here especially if you want to pay what food should cost and not the jacked up tourist prices.  Love Moon Wok!!

Food was really bad. Seasoning was just not there. They were out of EVERYTHING! Took forever for our check when we were clearly done. Our waiter was very nice and sweet. But this place was just not the Chinese food that we wanted.
Good food just wish they had more.

(Translated by Google) Delicious food, attention 10 and very good location all at a super accessible price, great place  (Original) Comida riquisima, la atención un 10 y muy buena localización todo a un precio súper accesible, gran lugar
Amazing place! Super affordable and tasty!
Good food
Sweet waitress and cheap food. Tasted ok too
Our waitress was so polite and the food was fantastic.   Took a bit of time but only 2 people were working at the time.  She checked on us and apologized multiple times.  Will return
Lovely menu with great prices! Love the Sesame Chicken and the Bhan Mi

So the tofu banh mi gets 5 stars along with the veggie pho. The rest of their food is actually the worst I have ever had and it pains me to say that because it's cheap, in a great location, and the employees are amazing. The veggie tofu and shrimp lo mein are terrible. The sauces are watery with no flavor and taste really weird....there isn't enough soy sauce in the world to help it. I'm pretty sure the lo mein is actually spaghetti. Gross spaghetti. I haven't eaten all day and I'm just going to make something else at home. It's all going in the trash. This breaks my heart.  I got the crab rangoons as well previously and they had this sweet, weird cheese in it with an odd texture and no crab at all. It tasted like old cheesecake filling and the dough was rubbery.
Very tasty!
This place is so good, I’ve inhaled everything I’ve ordered from them I just wish they were open later

The food is really good. I do go there sometimes. But I mostly get my food to go. The decor isn't what you'd think, with it being in the French Quarter. The people that work there are very nice though. Food comes out nice and fresh, while being done in a timely manner
Best lil Chinese place  hidden gem in New Orleans fresh food and superb pork meat egg rolls the usual ones r handmade and get this very reasonable
I got angel hair noodles with soy sauce and mushy vegetables as lomein. Crab rangoon was overcooked and wontons were super hard. NEVER AGAIN
Good food at a reasonable price!  What more do you need?

My friend and I ate at China Moon Wok Restaurant and the food was delicious! The waitress had great customer service! My friend ordered the Sesame chicken, and I ordered the Sweet and Sour chicken. We both enjoyed eating our food. I highly recommend eating at China Moon Wok!

If I could give negative stars I would. I read most of the reviews and figures the one star ones were just haters. We are local and figured the locals seem to like it. If you find this food in any way shape or form good, you do not have taste buds. The Generals Tsos chicken was just chicken in a buffalo sauce. If I wanted wings I’d have gotten them elsewhere. The fried rice had no tase and the sesame chicken was soggy. I do NOT get how people think this is good. They also accidentally put someone else’s vermicelli bowl in our order. I figured I’d try that instead of the chicken. Nasty. The sauce for the vermicelli bowl was pure vinegar. Go eat a Lucky Dog instead. 🤮🤮🤮🤮

I ordered hot and spicy soup, stir fried vegetables with the egg roll for my lunch and it was HORRIBLE! The wontons that came with the soup were fried in old grease and the fortune cookie was stale. The soup was thick and had a taste like it was old. I will never order from here again! EVER!
Amazing food & great service! Will definitely be back.

Bao, the cashier and waiter, is super experience and actually knows a lot about New Orleans. You coming for the food, and you get great commentary and people skills from him! The first time I went in there, it was a little bit dirty, but the food was fantastic. I come from Pensacola, and I've eaten all the Vietnamese food there. But I went to a random hole in the wall place like China moonwalk restaurant in New Orleans, and the food was 3 times better than in Pensacola. Not an intidepensicola. But this place has been here for a long time, past hurricane Katrina. They know what they're doing. I stayed there for much longer, and watched Sharknado movies of strangers, and I connected a lot to just random people who love the food. I went back to New Orleans with another group of people and introduce them to the restaurant and made another set of different friends. Thanks China moonwalk, for making my New Orleans trip more homie!
Great and authentic Vietnamese and Chinese food.
Vegetarian friendly. Really nice Pho. The place might seem closed from out but it's open. It does close after lunch and not sure if they serve dinner.

dude used spaghetti noodles in my lo mein? and there were onions in the crab rangoon? not very cool. bathroom was gross. gave my leftovers to a homeless guy down the street. the guy working there was nice tho!
Best pho in NOLA! Just have weird hours. Always showing up when they're closed. I'll have to keep a picture in my phone for reference.

Reading the reviews before arriving was a bit scary, needless to say, but the food was ok. I ordered the vegetarian low mein but there wasn’t much soup in it. The noodle flavor was decent but the broccoli and tofu tasted a bit off. Although, the staff were kind and made sure to ask how you were doing. Just take an extra look if you order meat.
Love this place

I’ve been here quite a few times. Im a local. DEFINITELY my always go to for Chinese. Very inexpensive and authentic Chinese! not frozen Chinese you get from nasty red apple or golden wall. It’s a hole in the wall, you wouldn’t expect the food to be as fantastic as it is from the way it looks so PLEASE don’t judge this place. I travel all over the cities for good crab Rangoon and THIS IS THE PLACE!
Very nice

Really tasty and reasonably priced! I've eaten here several times and tried the orange chicken, mandarin chicken and crab rangoon. Chicken is always crispy and the sauce is amazing. Highly recommended!
Great Pho
Good taste
Amazing the best Chinese food I’ve had in a while..and the best customer service

The food was very tasty and cheap! wow, this was one of the most reasonable places to eat, the place itself was not very clean and fancy, but the nice young man made this place worth coming in to eat, he made us feel so comfortable and welcomed us with such a friendly face and attitude, well worth the five stars.

We had delicious dinner here, food was really good price as well! The couple who own this little corner place are super friendly and made the visit that much better. If you’re in the French Quarter area I would definitely give this a try! I had honey chicken and it was yummy.
General Tso chicken is delicious. Best in the city. I have only ordered to-go, but this is the best general tso’s chicken that I have ever had!!

Don’t eat here. Opened the box to a giant, thick black hair.  Egg rolls smelled like bath water.  Weird mini shrimps in the rice looked like uncooked Nemo’s. The shrimp in the lo mein tasted horrid as well. All around a horrible experience. Save ur monies and go for the Popeyes instead.
The chicken was still crispy with the sauce and it was so delicious!
Good food with nice flavor but the building in desperate need of a make over, the place is a dumped and old..
Local Chinese restaurant, a small place serving big platters of good Chinese food. Plan on taking leftovers home.
Always friendly
Nice food from a family owned restaurant with super low prices.
The food was fine and the bathroom was the nastiest bathroom I have ever seen. You couldnt even sit on the toilet the right way, you had to sit sideways. Also no tissue.

The food is horrible! I am completely annoyed by the taste. I ordered sesame seed chicken with shrimp fried rice, the sauce on the chicken taste horrible and they added to much of it. The rice looked like yellow rice that didn’t go with the soy sauce. Omg the freaking egg roll was burnt and I picked at the whole plate. Thank god for cafe Du Monde and their beignets bc I would’ve been starving at work.

With all of the flair in same ole same ol food all around New Orleans French quarter this place is an absolute gem and I not only appreciate a food to fullest extent but they customized it to my taste and  order and it is also at a most reasonable price which is very different from most every damm thing in the French quarter, I totally recommend it and of eating here 2nd day in a row. Addendum 4th day IN A ROW.... I love this restaurant,  I have invited the entire staff to come stay with us in Florida, if anyone has somerhing bad to say about this restaurant or these folk,  they are inept! FIGGT ME! Love love love Chima Moon Wok, KT, Bau and Hang!
Nice people-cheapest you will get food in the area
Excellent food and service. Friendly staff. Quick and delicious. Recommended for anyone who loves good food.
Food is great, great service
Nice folks, but food was terrible!!! Two different dishes, both swimming in the same red sauce, not good.
Good, no-frills, hole-in-the-wall serving consistently tasty Asian food.  Been around a long time.  Staff is friendly also.
I ordered a hot and spicy soup to go but got egg drop soup.  The soup was super salty and I ended up not eating it.  The almond boneless chicken and Vietnamese spring rolls were oily and again salty.
Good food good prices
The service was outstanding! Food was good & portions were satisfactory.  I hard the Vietnamese Pork & Ham sandwich, and the sesame steak bowl, and I'd eat here again!
Nice

The Vietnamese vermicelli was amazing.  The fish sauce top notch.  The staff was incredibly amazing, attentive and kind. I am not used to “southern iced tea” as it is brewed pretty sweet.  I asked to change it out and they were apologetic, even though it was my fault.  I should have known better.  I’m used to unsweet (Northerner here). The portions are substantial and being a 6’3 over 300# big guy I am stuffed.  The orange chicken was good but if you have a chance try the homemade duck sauce.  Knock your socks off. Thank you guys for a great meal, quick courteous service and for excising my southern tea faux paw.  YOU GOTTA TRY THIS PLACE.  Ignore the naysayers, they were likely drunk and being ignorant.  ;)
Good, cheap lunch in the quarter. 6.95 gets you an entree w/ rice and an egg roll. I come here quite a bit, and will continue to do so.
Good food good people good atmosphere but the plates are more bean sprout and cabbage than anything kind if a rip off

We never ordered any food after we walked in. If you eat here you should take a look at the place first. It is very hard to believe they cook with hygiene in mind when you see the place. Your stomach gives you the feeling like you wont be able to get out of bed the next day. Maybe this is not the case but we wont take our chances.
Delicious food and vintage environment.

I came back to give Moon Wok a try after a desperate need for White Rice to go along with my leftover Thai food. My first attempt back, My coworker ordered pork fried rice and I ordered white rice . Picked it up. Came back to work and to my surprise, a failed attempt at rice. I don’t know what brand they use, but the rice was very mushy at top, and hard at the bottom with brown remnants from the RicePot with a few lonely pieces of what I think was green onion.  Second attempt. Same thing.  I appreciate this business for being a form of affordable Asian cuisine in the French Quarters but pls. Owners/Chefs not at the price of ruining the culture and experience for its supports. Invest in a better rice pot, quality rice, ingredients and bang! I’ll be back. The customer service is there. The prices are there. The taste tho, needs some serious attention and solution.

This was the worst Chinese food I’ve ever had. It took longer than they said to deliver it. There was a hair cooked into a piece of chicken. The shrimp had a weird taste to it. Even the fortune cookies were stale. When I called to tell them about the hair in the food the guy was rude.  Avoid at all costs if possible!!

Great food made fresh and made to order at incredible prices. Fried rice is cooked perfectly. Shrimp is local Louisiana shrimp and is never overcooked. Fresh spring rolls are large, taste great and super inexpensive. I highly recommend this family owned and operated restaurant.
Excellent customer service, food was very good and prices are unbelievably reasonable,  I will certainly be back
I live next door and love this place!  My go to for quick bites and full meals.
Should be condemned
Best sweet and sour chicken. Best service...the food during Mardi Gras is the best street food. Best Best Best.
Great service. Great food. Great price
Food was very delicious & service was great!!
(Translated by Google) My good  (Original) Miy bueno
Dope and inexpensive
Just visiting and we decided to try this restaurant. I'm very glad we did as it was some of the best soup and sweet and sour chicken we've had!
After hearing so many great things about this place, I was disappointed in the food. It wasn't nasty... Just normal
(Translated by Google) Okay  (Original) Bueno

Hole in the wall atmosphere accentuates this New Orleans Far Eastern cuisine staple in nothing less but the best ways. Moon Wok is a hidden gem in New Orleans. Very helpful staff; as a vegetarian, the hostess provided me with delightful options. As a local, Moon Wok is amongst my first choices when I'm feeling hangry in the Quarter!
Food is good.  Limited hours.  Fairly consistent experience.
Small inexpensive good fresh food!....service great!...very friendly staff...family owned

I went there with my sister to order take out. I ordered the beef pho, some fried shrimp, and 2 egg rolls and she ordered sweet and sour chicken and it came with an egg roll. we waited for a bit which is no problem. We took our food home and the pho was fine but the egg roll was sour and some of the shrimp had a bad taste. My sister's egg roll was sour too. Now I'm constantly throwing up my guts, my stomach has sharp pains and I can't keep anything down. I hope they improve.. until then I won't ever be coming back.
I live nearby and this place is among my favorites. Food is cheap, fast, and delicious. I recommend the fried rice, spring rolls, and the General Tso's Chicken (best I have ever had).
Love this place good food and great prices
Very dirty on the inside. The fortune cookie was the best food.
Worst lo mein ever, they served shrimp over linguini instead of lo mein noodles. I will never go back.

Ordered off of Uber Eats, most of the food was edible, the Egg Drop Soup, however, was horrible. I called the restaurant to tell them they should check the eggs they used because it tasted rancid, (not being dramatic, the egg tasted rotten and was a weird orange color), and I had to argue with the host to talk to a manager because of how crazy busy they were. The amount of time it took for this kid to argue how busy the restaurant was, he could've told the manager about 30 times that there was a call for them. Once he finally got someone, (spoiler, it wasn't the manager), the woman he got told me they'd refund me for the soup withing 20 seconds of conversation. I gratefully accepted the refund, and then told her she should check the soup so nobody gets sick. She then said, "We have sold out of it and nobody has complained besides you.", yeah,  because that's believable.
Tasty and fast
Horrible Chinese food, soggy, flavorless orange chicken, dried shrimp fried rice, if you wanna call it that, and hollow crab Rangoon, I'll never order it again!
Ordered broccoli and beef and sesame chicken. Worst chicken ever!  Restaurant and ladies room were filthy.
Worst Chinese food we ever had. The lo mein was sour, the portions were off, and the wait was so long. We only could stomach a few bites.

I love dive restaurants but this one serves food on the same level as the septic state of its dining room, kitchen and bathroom. I had the orange  chicken with mushy steamed rice and floury orange sauce. Egg roll was inedible, tasted slightly off.
My favorite Chinese restaurant in the French Quarter.  Fast and friendly staff.
Staff are amazing.
Decent food, fair prices. Odd hours make lunch difficult
Great place to get a quick, cheap bite. I've walked out stuffed to the gills for under 10 bucks.
A hidden gem. Worth going early before they close. Best spring rolls around.
Best drunk Chinese ever
Good for drunk food.

This restaurant is awful. Fair warning: the couple that run the restaurant live in the apartment directly above it and own a dog that they never take out. Because of their neglect, the poor dog is forced to urinate on the downward sloping balcony. Consequently, restaurant patrons and innocent passersby run the risk of being peed on while they walk. I have witnessed this happen on multiple occasions. Do yourself a favor and eat at one of the other thousands of restaurants in this city that doesn't come with a urine shower.

I use to eat the Pho here (2yrs ago)which is probably the only decent food here. But now I'll never eat here again. I ordered orange chicken & i got soggy mush. Go get your Vietnamese food elsewhere. Pho orchid is awesome!

Ordered food, had it delivered and it was pretty ridiculous. Aside from being hungover and willing to eat anything for breakfast, this lo mein was freaking angel hair pasta! Italian pasta with so.e soy sauce on top!! NUFF SAID.
Food was horrible... Spring Rolls are disgusting like eating rubber..orange chicken disgusting.. Wish i could put half a star

The food was okay for cheap Chinese. I'm not sure whether it's a coincidence or not, but...my friends and I ate here. Those of us who paid with a card had fraudulent charges on our account just a day or two later. It was the only place that all of us had in common...so I guess just don't use a card if you eat here to be on the safe side.
One of my favorite spots in the quarter to grab foodm usually for the banh mi. Staff is always great too!
Always good food. A hole in the wall restaurant with character and really good prices. Good place to escape to when everything else is busy.
The best in new orleans
It's cheap and decent. Not the best asian food, but probably the best in the quarter

I live in the quarter and I understand the hateful reviews. They have some tasty things, some of the cheap greasy items we crave on fat ass movie days/nights and then... I don't know what they're thinking. We ordered their lomain and got angel hair pasta. When we called regarding this, they tried to tell us they've always used that. NO, Lomain is the type of noodle. If it's not Lomain,don't call it Lomain. They're a frustrating last ditch of Chinese food cravings, but you're better off ordering from someplace that consistently provides what they advertise

This restaurant, though in appearance a bit iffy, puts out very good food.  I read the recent reviews and find them quite unkind and unfair.  This place has been in business at least 10 years, and if the negative reviews were true, the locals would have run this place out of town.  This place has a strong local following, and when I 've dined in the place, I end up talking with other patrons singing their praise.  Haters stay home

Basic American Chinese food if you're wasted; however, watching the owners let their dogs urinate on the balcony over the restaurant daily gives me great concern as to health practices in the restaurant.

What a dump! Don't waste your money. The food is absolutely garbage. There are not enough words to describe it. The outside looks bad, the inside looks even worse. I can't understand how they can keep the doors open.
I ordered the orange chicken with fried rice and crab ragoons.  Worst I've ever had. But at least the guy came back and refunded my myoney.

Gees.   I really wanted to give these guys a fighting chance.  I'm a huge advocate of small restaurant / hole-in-the-wall establishments, and I know everyone has an "off" day, but man they were bad.  By bad I mean, aweful / dirty ambience (which can be overlooked since this IS "The Quarter").  Food that will put you in the hospital.  Seriously.  I ordered a beef Entree.  Fortunately the lack of seasoning caused me to notice (from about 3 feet away) the sour smell of rancid beef.  It seriously smelled like something died in my bowl. I am a huge fan of traditional Asian meals (I am Asian and was raised on Asian food).  I was too self conscious (I know, I'm a dumbass) to send it back right away. Alas, it was so pretty and well-plated that after 2 unsuccessful attempts at ingesting this rotting corpse, I had to send it back.  I ordered a sandwich instead.  Well now, here I am after having spent the following day with "it coming out at both ends".  Yeah you know what I mean.  I live alone with my son, this is the only meal we haven't eaten together (thank God -I usually cook at home).  Doc says it was definitely something I ate within the last 48 hours.  This place sucks.  Hands down.  If you want to attempt suicide by "the Hershey Squirts" I recommend this place.  There are plenty of other Chinese/ Authentic Vietnamese in town.  Try any of the places on Decatur (Samurai Sushi / Ginger Lime, etc.).  Seriously, you've been warned!
The food was great considering the low price. The service was wonderful though and the location was very charming.

Not the best Chinese/Vietnamese food I've ever eaten, but if you are in the mood for that and do not want to drive to NO East or meander around the West Bank then Moon Wok has you covered. they also deliver in the French Quarter and Marigny triangle.  The Vietnamese food is better than the Chinese food.  Vegetarian and vegan friendly.
